---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Android Support - Strollcast">
  <header>
    <h1>Android App Support</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Get help using the Strollcast Android app</p>
  </header>

  <section class="content">
    <h2>Voice Commands</h2>
    <p>
      The Strollcast Android app supports hands-free voice control for playback. You can use voice commands to pause, play, skip forward/backward, and check what's currently playing.
    </p>

    <div class="important-note">
      <span class="note-icon">‚ö†Ô∏è</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Important: Google Assistant Required</strong>
        <p>
          Voice commands work with <strong>Google Assistant</strong>, not Google Gemini. If Gemini is your default assistant, voice commands will not work. You need to switch back to Google Assistant to use voice control features.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h3>Supported Voice Commands</h3>
    <div class="command-list">
      <div class="command">
        <code>"Hey Google, pause in Stroll Cast"</code>
        <span>Pause playback</span>
      </div>
      <div class="command">
        <code>"Hey Google, play in Stroll Cast"</code>
        <span>Resume playback</span>
      </div>
      <div class="command">
        <code>"Hey Google, skip forward 15 seconds in Stroll Cast"</code>
        <span>Skip ahead</span>
      </div>
      <div class="command">
        <code>"Hey Google, skip backward 15 seconds in Stroll Cast"</code>
        <span>Go back</span>
      </div>
      <div class="command">
        <code>"Hey Google, what's playing in Stroll Cast?"</code>
        <span>Show current episode info</span>
      </div>
      <div class="command">
        <code>"Hey Google, jump to reference in Stroll Cast"</code>
        <span>Play referenced episode from transcript</span>
      </div>
      <div class="command">
        <code>"Hey Google, play previous in Stroll Cast"</code>
        <span>Go back to previous episode</span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>How to Switch from Gemini to Google Assistant</h2>
    <p>
      If Google Gemini is your default assistant, follow these steps to switch back to Google Assistant:
    </p>

    <h3>Method 1: Through the Gemini App</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Open the <strong>Gemini app</strong> on your Android phone</li>
      <li>Tap your <strong>profile photo</strong> or initial at the top right</li>
      <li>Tap <strong>Settings</strong></li>
      <li>Scroll down and tap <strong>"Digital assistants from Google"</strong></li>
      <li>Select <strong>Google Assistant</strong></li>
      <li>Confirm the change</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Method 2: Through Android Settings</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>Open your Android <strong>Settings</strong></li>
      <li>Go to <strong>Google</strong> or <strong>Google Services</strong></li>
      <li>Tap <strong>All services</strong></li>
      <li>Tap <strong>Search, Assistant, and Voice</strong></li>
      <li>Tap <strong>Gemini</strong></li>
      <li>Tap <strong>Digital Assistants from Google</strong></li>
      <li>Select <strong>Google Assistant</strong> as the default option</li>
      <li>Confirm the change</li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Verification</h3>
    <p>
      After switching, test that Google Assistant is active:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Say "Hey, Google" or hold down the power button</li>
      <li>You should see <strong>Google Assistant</strong> interface (not Gemini)</li>
      <li>Try a voice command: "Hey Google, pause in Stroll Cast" while playing</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="tip">
      <span class="tip-icon">üí°</span>
      <div>
        <strong>Tip</strong>
        <p>
          You can still use Gemini by opening the Gemini app directly. Switching your default assistant only affects voice activation and hardware shortcuts.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>

    <h3>Voice commands still not working?</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Check that Strollcast is playing</strong> ‚Äî Voice commands only work when audio is actively playing</li>
      <li><strong>Verify Google Assistant</strong> ‚Äî Make sure you're using "Hey Google" and it opens Google Assistant, not Gemini</li>
      <li><strong>Use "Stroll Cast" in commands</strong> ‚Äî Say "in Stroll Cast" at the end of commands (not "Strollcast")</li>
      <li><strong>Check notification controls</strong> ‚Äî If you can pause/play from the notification, the media session is working correctly</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>App crashes or doesn't load episodes</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Check your internet connection</strong> ‚Äî Episodes need to be downloaded or streamed</li>
      <li><strong>Clear app cache</strong> ‚Äî Settings ‚Üí Apps ‚Üí Strollcast ‚Üí Storage ‚Üí Clear Cache</li>
      <li><strong>Update the app</strong> ‚Äî Make sure you have the latest version</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>More Help</h2>
    <p>
      For additional support or to report issues, visit our <a href="https://github.com/strollcast/StrollcastApp/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Issues</a> page.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  header {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .subtitle {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .content {
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .content h2 {
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }

  .content h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .content h3 {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  ol, ul {
    margin: 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  ol li, ul li {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding-left: 0;
  }

  ul li {
    position: relative;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  ul li::before {
    content: "‚Üí";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  .important-note {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    background: #fff8e1;
    border-left: 4px solid #ffc107;
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .note-icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .important-note strong {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    color: #333;
  }

  .important-note p {
    margin: 0;
    color: #666;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .command-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .command {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .command code {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .command span {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }

  .tip {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .tip-icon {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .tip strong {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .tip p {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .command {
      padding: 0.75rem;
    }

    .important-note {
      flex-direction: column;
      padding: 1rem;
    }
  }
</style>
